WEBVTT

00:02.070 --> 00:03.071
[ The Craig Gildner Sextet's
"Let's Be Jolly" plays ]

00:05.239 --> 00:06.874
* Well, tonight's the night

00:06.907 --> 00:09.177
* We a-get to see, oh, Santa
[ Laughs ]

00:09.210 --> 00:10.244
Mm-hmm.

00:10.278 --> 00:12.480
[ Laughs ]
Hey, guys.
Hi.

00:12.513 --> 00:14.982
Happy Christmas Eve, Mike.
Happy Hanukkah Eve, Rio.

00:15.015 --> 00:17.418
Thank you, Rudy.
Thank you for seeing me.

00:17.451 --> 00:20.721
Rio, I stocked some
Jewish decorations for you.

00:20.754 --> 00:22.190
[ Gasps ]
Oh, that is
so thoughtful.

00:22.223 --> 00:24.858
So, these are not
Stars of David.

00:24.892 --> 00:27.328
These are, uh...
satanic pentagrams.

00:27.361 --> 00:28.729
Oh, dear.

00:28.762 --> 00:30.030
That makes sense now.

00:30.064 --> 00:31.999
There was talk about "The Beast"
on the website.

00:32.032 --> 00:33.067
I'm so sorry.

00:33.101 --> 00:34.102
Oh, the Dark Lord, sure.
Oh.

00:34.135 --> 00:35.236
But they're very lovely.

00:35.269 --> 00:36.337
Why are you two
still here?

00:36.370 --> 00:37.438
Shouldn't you be
with family?

00:37.471 --> 00:38.606
We're --
We're kinda doing

00:38.639 --> 00:40.007
Christmas alone
together, and...

00:40.040 --> 00:41.709
Yeah.
It's our first Christmas
in Bucksnort.

00:41.742 --> 00:42.910
And I'm gonna cook
a goose.

00:42.943 --> 00:44.678
I ordered one --
a real beautiful bird,

00:44.712 --> 00:46.347
from a boutique
organic market...
He ordered a goose.

00:46.380 --> 00:48.716
...just outside of Dubuque.
Why?

00:48.749 --> 00:51.018
Frank has got a whole pond full
of geese, and he hates them.

00:51.051 --> 00:53.121
Oh, well, maybe next year,
I'll -- I'll bag one of those.
Oh. [ Chuckles ] Yeah.

00:53.154 --> 00:55.589
Okay, $5.50.

00:55.623 --> 00:57.225
Brandon's gone,
so I'm gonna be at Connie's.

00:57.258 --> 00:58.859
Rio: Okay.
So, don't try a-knockin',

00:58.892 --> 01:00.528
'cause Connie's
gonna be a-rockin'.

01:00.561 --> 01:02.630
The first time
I'm going to lay her.
Oh!

01:02.663 --> 01:05.366
Oh, that's information
that we're getting.
Constance: Yeah.

01:05.399 --> 01:06.967
Not if I lay him first.

01:07.000 --> 01:08.068
[ Laughs ]
All right, we're gonna go
watch the lights.

01:08.102 --> 01:09.437
All right?
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

01:09.470 --> 01:12.906
* Away in a manger

01:12.940 --> 01:16.577
* No crib for a bed

01:16.610 --> 01:19.580
* The little lord Jesus

01:19.613 --> 01:21.249
Why is Clara
the only one singing?

01:21.282 --> 01:23.484
Oh, 'cause she's been
drinking beer since noon.

01:23.517 --> 01:27.155
[ Off-key ]
* Look down where he lay

01:27.188 --> 01:28.222
* The li--

01:28.256 --> 01:29.590
Okay, everybody.
Rio: Oh.

01:29.623 --> 01:30.591
"Merry Christmas" on three.

01:30.624 --> 01:32.760
One, two, three!

01:32.793 --> 01:35.196
All: Merry Christmas!

01:36.364 --> 01:37.765
[ Electricity buzzes ]

01:37.798 --> 01:39.467
Mike: Oh.
Rio: Oh!

01:39.500 --> 01:41.469
Lot -- Lot of build-up.
Yeah, a lot of pageantry.

01:41.502 --> 01:42.470
Yeah.

01:42.503 --> 01:44.772
Here we go!

01:44.805 --> 01:45.773
[ Electricity buzzes ]

01:45.806 --> 01:47.007
[ Cheers and applause ]

01:47.040 --> 01:48.576
Now we're
getting somewhere!

01:48.609 --> 01:50.077
Now we're talking.

01:50.110 --> 01:51.845
This one goes out
to the kitties.

01:51.879 --> 01:53.113
[ To tune of
"Away in a Manger" ]
* Meow, meow

01:53.147 --> 01:55.983
* Meow-meow, meow, meow

01:56.016 --> 01:58.352
* Meow-meow, meow, meow, meow

01:58.386 --> 01:59.187
I'll bite.

01:59.220 --> 02:00.521
* Meow, meow

02:00.554 --> 02:03.023
All:
* Meow-meow, meow, meow

02:03.056 --> 02:05.326
* Meow, meow, meow, meow, meow

02:05.359 --> 02:06.327
Do it.

02:06.360 --> 02:10.130
**

02:10.164 --> 02:13.133
-- Captions by VITAC --

02:13.167 --> 02:16.670
**

02:16.704 --> 02:18.839
Honey, I love this sculpture
that your family sent.

02:18.872 --> 02:21.775
Did Santa actually visit
the baby Jesus?

02:21.809 --> 02:23.143
Uh, with Christmas,
in general,

02:23.177 --> 02:24.812
it's best not to ask
how the sausage is made.

02:24.845 --> 02:26.814
Just enjoy the yummy sausage.
Sure, yeah.

02:26.847 --> 02:28.115
Merry Christmas, roommates.

02:28.148 --> 02:29.617
Look at this
jolly gentleman.

02:29.650 --> 02:31.952
The time has come.
I'm off to Kay's.

02:31.985 --> 02:34.955
Jacob deserves a Christmas
with both parents...
Sure.

02:34.988 --> 02:36.557
...and I am going
to deliver.

02:36.590 --> 02:39.227
Also, I'm gonna deliver for Kay
a custard pie.

02:39.260 --> 02:40.328
We're really proud
of you, Beau.

02:40.361 --> 02:42.230
You were this caterpillar,
you know?

02:42.263 --> 02:44.064
And now you've blossomed
to be this -- this butterfly,

02:44.097 --> 02:45.666
and it's really beautiful
to see.
Yeah.

02:45.699 --> 02:46.834
I am a butterfly,
aren't I?

02:46.867 --> 02:47.835
Yeah.
I'm like a --

02:47.868 --> 02:49.703
a very sexy butterfly
with --

02:49.737 --> 02:51.539
with big butterfly muscles...
Mm.

02:51.572 --> 02:54.542
and -- and -- and great
butterfly masculine instincts.

02:54.575 --> 02:56.076
[ Chuckling ] Yeah.
A-A ripped monarch.

02:56.109 --> 02:56.977
All right!
Go get 'em!
[ Laughs ]
[ Door opens ]

02:57.010 --> 02:58.246
That's sweet.

02:58.279 --> 02:59.313
You know what else
is sweet?

02:59.347 --> 03:00.581
Huh?

03:00.614 --> 03:02.716
Listen to
that sound.

03:02.750 --> 03:05.853
It's the sound of no Beau
and no Rudy in this house.

03:05.886 --> 03:07.154
Oh, my goodness.

03:07.187 --> 03:09.323
You're right.
There's no snoring.

03:09.357 --> 03:10.524
There's no yelling.
No.

03:10.558 --> 03:11.725
No one's arguing about

03:11.759 --> 03:13.661
whether Ronald Reagan
was a good actor.

03:13.694 --> 03:15.996
It's like, "Who cares?"
Who cares?

03:16.029 --> 03:18.499
Ahh! Yeah.
So peaceful and relaxing.

03:18.532 --> 03:21.034
We're pretty overdue
for some alone time.
Yeah.

03:21.068 --> 03:22.903
Mm.
Ooh, you know
what I'm gonna do?

03:22.936 --> 03:24.738
I'm gonna take a bath.
You know what I mean?
Oh.

03:24.772 --> 03:26.440
I'm gonna have to go upstairs
and first, like,

03:26.474 --> 03:27.875
sort of scrub the Rudy and Beau
off the bath.

03:27.908 --> 03:29.076
Sure.
But then I'm gonna
take a bath.

03:29.109 --> 03:30.378
I'll be in the kitchen...
Okay.

03:30.411 --> 03:32.346
...preparing
our fancy-ass dinner...
[ Gasps ]

03:32.380 --> 03:33.881
...that I mail-ordered...
[ Squeals ]

03:33.914 --> 03:34.948
...'cause it's
goose-glazing time.

03:34.982 --> 03:36.350
I can't wait.
Yes. Okay.

03:36.384 --> 03:37.217
Uh, by the way, it's gonna --
it's gonna take

03:37.251 --> 03:38.519
about three hours.
That's all right.

03:38.552 --> 03:40.120
It's gonna take me three hours
to scrub the tub.

03:40.153 --> 03:41.121
Oh, wonderful.
So, it works out.

03:41.154 --> 03:42.189
That'll time out beautifully.
Yeah.

03:42.222 --> 03:46.427
**

03:46.460 --> 03:49.196
Beau, did you bake?
Wait, are you wearing my apron?

03:49.229 --> 03:50.364
If you're doing
an impression of me,

03:50.398 --> 03:51.699
I'm not interested, okay?

03:51.732 --> 03:53.066
I'm not in the mood
to be mocked.

03:53.100 --> 03:54.134
I'm just putting
the finishing touches

03:54.167 --> 03:55.269
on these cookie tins.

03:55.303 --> 03:56.870
I know it usually takes
most of your day,

03:56.904 --> 03:58.439
so I wanted to get
a jump-start on that.

03:58.472 --> 04:00.541
I also threw away
my beer-can ornament collection

04:00.574 --> 04:01.742
that you hate.

04:01.775 --> 04:03.644
Even the Santa
with the swim trunks

04:03.677 --> 04:05.613
who's pouring a beer
over his head?
Yeah.

04:05.646 --> 04:07.214
And Margaritaville?
Uh-huh.

04:07.247 --> 04:09.116
The one that plays
"I Got Friends in Low Places"?

04:09.149 --> 04:10.751
Did you like that one?
No.

04:10.784 --> 04:11.619
You liked some of them.

04:11.652 --> 04:12.886
Didn't like any of them.

04:12.920 --> 04:14.588
Okay, they're gone.
I wrapped the gifts.

04:14.622 --> 04:17.325
Uh, you got Jacob
a Jason Statham Blu-ray set.

04:17.358 --> 04:19.259
Actually, I did
my own shopping this year.

04:19.293 --> 04:20.961
Hey, Jacob,
we're doing gifts!

04:20.994 --> 04:22.663
What do you mean
you did your --

04:22.696 --> 04:24.832
You bought that yourself?
I still get gifts
this year?

04:24.865 --> 04:26.066
Yeah.
I-I just --

04:26.099 --> 04:27.668
I thought maybe broken homes
didn't do it.

04:27.701 --> 04:29.136
This is so exciting!

04:29.169 --> 04:30.971
Okay, well, Jacob,
just to be clear --

04:31.004 --> 04:32.573
I-I get it, Mom.
I know.

04:32.606 --> 04:34.107
Just because Dad's home
does not mean

04:34.141 --> 04:35.443
that you guys
are getting back together.

04:35.476 --> 04:37.077
I know. I just want
to enjoy the holidays.

04:37.110 --> 04:38.612
That's good,
because...

04:38.646 --> 04:41.582
happiness is a journey,
not a destination.

04:41.615 --> 04:43.150
The Buddha.

04:43.183 --> 04:44.518
Yeah, that's something Rio
repeats all the time.

04:44.552 --> 04:49.457
**

04:49.490 --> 04:50.290
A key?

04:53.461 --> 04:55.329
An ATV?

04:55.363 --> 04:57.130
Yeah!!

04:57.164 --> 04:59.933
[ Laughs ]
Oh, my gosh!

04:59.967 --> 05:02.603
Well, that is a very
thoughtful and generous gift.

05:02.636 --> 05:04.638
Okay, take it for a spin.
Yes!

05:04.672 --> 05:06.974
Love you guys!
Golly!

05:07.007 --> 05:08.041
Okay, you, uh...
[ Clears throat ]

05:08.075 --> 05:09.710
...need any help
in the kitchen?

05:09.743 --> 05:12.380
Do I need any what?

05:12.413 --> 05:13.714
Help.

05:13.747 --> 05:15.616
I can't hear you.
Say it again.

05:15.649 --> 05:16.650
Do you need help?

05:16.684 --> 05:17.618
[ Voice breaking ] Help?

05:17.651 --> 05:18.652
One more time.

05:18.686 --> 05:19.953
I would like
to help you.

05:19.987 --> 05:22.189
[ Sighing ] Ohh.
Pregnant Mary on the donkey.

05:22.222 --> 05:24.492
Rudy: You can do this.
You can do this.

05:24.525 --> 05:26.660
**

05:26.694 --> 05:27.795
Merry Christmas!

05:27.828 --> 05:29.029
[ Screams ]

05:29.062 --> 05:30.564
Constance: Geez.

05:30.598 --> 05:32.800
Rudy,
this is my mama.

05:32.833 --> 05:34.902
So, you're
the new boyfriend?

05:34.935 --> 05:36.704
Please, God,
don't unwrap me.

05:36.737 --> 05:38.338
Rudy: In retrospect,

05:38.372 --> 05:40.641
this was a colossal
error in judgment.

05:40.674 --> 05:43.143
Just curious, at your age,
how's your eyesight?

05:43.176 --> 05:44.478
20/20.

05:44.512 --> 05:46.213
Rudy, Mama just got here
an hour ago,

05:46.246 --> 05:48.816
and it was quite a surprise.
Oh. Mm-hmm.

05:48.849 --> 05:51.251
Constance wouldn't
tell me much about you,

05:51.284 --> 05:53.186
so I feared the worst.

05:53.220 --> 05:57.257
Is that what social media
has done to your generation?

05:57.290 --> 05:58.426
Okay, aside from that
pornographic event

05:58.459 --> 06:00.227
that you bore witness to,
I can assure you...

06:00.260 --> 06:01.895
I'm an upstanding
gentleman.

06:01.929 --> 06:04.532
Well, Constance
is my pride and joy.

06:04.565 --> 06:08.068
My one wish is that
she be well taken care of.

06:08.101 --> 06:10.103
So, Mr. Rudy,
you got a job?

06:10.137 --> 06:11.672
Oh, boy.
Where you live?

06:11.705 --> 06:13.106
[ Chuckles nervously ]
You rent or own?

06:13.140 --> 06:15.175
Oh, dear.
And what about savings?

06:15.208 --> 06:16.944
"Yes."

06:16.977 --> 06:21.014
[ Chuckles nervously ] Mama,
Rudy's a very successful farmer.

06:21.048 --> 06:22.750
That's right.
Right.

06:22.783 --> 06:24.885
And I have a diverse
investment portfolio, too,

06:24.918 --> 06:27.755
that includes stocks,
paper money, gold bullion.

06:27.788 --> 06:30.458
I keep it all in a giant house
on a desirable street.

06:30.491 --> 06:31.725
Is that so?

06:31.759 --> 06:35.228
[ Chuckles nervously ]
Yeah.

06:35.262 --> 06:37.130
[ Chuckles ]
[ Door opens ]

06:37.164 --> 06:38.866
Please don't contradict the lies
I'm about to tell.

06:38.899 --> 06:39.900
What are y--

06:39.933 --> 06:41.469
Welcome to my home!

06:41.502 --> 06:43.704
Mama,
this is Rudy's farm.

06:43.737 --> 06:44.872
Mm.

06:44.905 --> 06:46.273
And who are
these people?

06:46.306 --> 06:49.643
Um...
Yeah, who --
who are we, Rudy?

06:55.048 --> 06:56.349
Mike and Rio used to
have their own farm, but
they lost it, like morons.

06:57.350 --> 06:59.052
Now they live in my barn.

06:59.086 --> 07:01.221
Is that a picture
of a cat holding another cat?

07:01.254 --> 07:02.490
I love it.

07:02.523 --> 07:03.791
Help yourself.

07:05.325 --> 07:06.460
I showed Belle
my genitals.

07:06.494 --> 07:07.595
You what?

07:07.628 --> 07:08.829
No, no. No, no.
I did. I--

07:08.862 --> 07:10.564
You were supposed
to wrap it up for Connie,

07:10.598 --> 07:11.832
and now you --
Why would you...?

07:11.865 --> 07:14.134
She showed up in town.
I-I didn't know she'd be there.

07:14.167 --> 07:15.669
What, did you feel like she had
been left out of the gift?
She open-- She opened the door,

07:15.703 --> 07:16.737
and I was like this.

07:16.770 --> 07:18.238
I'm sorry.
I suggested he wrap up

07:18.271 --> 07:20.508
like a-a yule log
offering.

07:20.541 --> 07:21.975
And now I need to
convince my mom

07:22.009 --> 07:23.176
that Rudy
is good enough for me.

07:23.210 --> 07:25.979
Rudy, I want to keep this.
Go right ahead.

07:26.013 --> 07:27.414
[ Quietly ] How did
she get that off the wall?

07:27.447 --> 07:29.617
Excuse me, Rudy's servants.
Rio: Uh-huh.

07:29.650 --> 07:30.851
When is dinner?

07:30.884 --> 07:32.152
Oh, yes. Dinner.
Dinner.

07:32.185 --> 07:35.122
So, we have not
prepared anything

07:35.155 --> 07:37.324
specifically for you,
per se.

07:37.357 --> 07:39.292
[ Clears throat ]
Um...

07:39.326 --> 07:41.595
A-A-And yet --
And yet,

07:41.629 --> 07:46.700
we have a Christmas goose
that we have prepared.

07:46.734 --> 07:48.536
For thy.
Thy.

07:48.569 --> 07:50.003
Now put a pep
in your step.
Uh --

07:50.037 --> 07:50.771
I don't want to have
to beat you both.

07:50.804 --> 07:51.939
What?

07:51.972 --> 07:53.641
[ Engine revving ]

07:53.674 --> 07:56.677
[ Imitates engine revving ]

07:56.710 --> 07:58.879
[ Air hissing ]

08:01.381 --> 08:03.617
They put that valve
in an interesting place.

08:03.651 --> 08:04.785
[ Laughs ]

08:04.818 --> 08:06.554
But I'm not thinking
about that kinda stuff.

08:06.587 --> 08:08.321
It's Christmas.
Yeah.

08:08.355 --> 08:09.823
Thank you for everything
you did today.

08:09.857 --> 08:11.358
You're welcome.

08:11.391 --> 08:12.993
I'm sorry that you even feel
like you have to thank me.

08:13.026 --> 08:14.161
It's stuff I should've
been just doing

08:14.194 --> 08:15.996
most of the time anyway.

08:16.029 --> 08:17.631
But --
And I never thanked you.

08:17.665 --> 08:18.732
[ Engine revving in distance ]

08:18.766 --> 08:20.033
Shut -- Shut up.

08:20.067 --> 08:21.168
Shut up your mouth.

08:21.201 --> 08:23.203
My life was so much better
when you were in it.

08:23.236 --> 08:25.305
And I know why we are
where we are,

08:25.338 --> 08:27.207
but I just want you to know
that I accept that,

08:27.240 --> 08:29.743
and I'm grateful for you.

08:29.777 --> 08:31.178
[ Sighs ]

08:31.211 --> 08:31.979
[ Voice breaking ]
What did you just say?

08:32.012 --> 08:33.647
I'm grateful for you.

08:33.681 --> 08:34.915
Oh, my God.
Sweet baby Jesus in the hay.

08:34.948 --> 08:37.050
I've got four or five
more snowmen,

08:37.084 --> 08:38.218
if you want me
to blow those up.

08:38.251 --> 08:39.519
Mm-hmm.

08:39.553 --> 08:41.254
Or, um, put on
those Christmas pajamas

08:41.288 --> 08:43.190
that you bought me 15 years ago
that I refused to wear?

08:43.223 --> 08:44.224
Oh.

08:44.257 --> 08:45.225
I could mist
those poinsettias.

08:45.258 --> 08:46.660
They look like
they could use that.

08:46.694 --> 08:48.929
No, there's just one thing
I want from you right now.

08:48.962 --> 08:51.498
I want you to make love to me,
you son of a bitch.

08:51.531 --> 08:52.766
I agree.

08:52.800 --> 08:54.401
[ Engine revving ]

08:54.434 --> 08:56.269
Whoo!

08:56.303 --> 08:58.205
Ta-da.
Oh!

08:58.238 --> 09:00.207
This looks delicious!
Constance: Lovely.

09:00.240 --> 09:01.609
Thank you.
Oh. Yes.

09:01.642 --> 09:02.943
I hope you enjoy.

09:02.976 --> 09:05.012
Can you blend mine
with some water?

09:05.045 --> 09:06.914
Rio: Oh.
You -- You would like
a goose smoothie?

09:06.947 --> 09:08.882
Ooh, that sounds delicious.
I'll have one of those, too.

09:08.916 --> 09:11.118
That's not necessary.
We're fine to chew.

09:11.151 --> 09:12.886
Great.
[ Clears throat ]

09:12.920 --> 09:14.421
Are they eating
with us?

09:14.454 --> 09:17.691
**

09:17.725 --> 09:19.526
I'm sorry,
but you must leave.

09:19.559 --> 09:20.961
Just so
I'm tracking this,

09:20.994 --> 09:22.562
you want us
to go to the barn

09:22.596 --> 09:26.366
and not enjoy this goose
that we brined for six days

09:26.399 --> 09:27.434
and then
air-dried overnight

09:27.467 --> 09:28.936
so it would be
perfectly crisp?

09:28.969 --> 09:30.403
You'll eat hay,
and you'll enjoy it, too!

09:30.437 --> 09:31.538
Um...

09:31.571 --> 09:33.106
Yeah. Well...
As you wish.

09:33.140 --> 09:36.209
Yes.
I guess we are...

09:36.243 --> 09:38.612
going over to the barn
where we squat.

09:38.646 --> 09:40.113
I'm grabbing just
a goose leg --
Get.

09:40.147 --> 09:42.482
Out! You heard Mrs. Byrd.
You get now!

09:42.515 --> 09:43.550
The only thing
you're gonna taste

09:43.583 --> 09:44.551
is the back of my hand!

09:44.584 --> 09:45.552
Oh, wow.
Oh, my goodness.

09:45.585 --> 09:46.553
You get now!
Yes...sir.

09:46.586 --> 09:47.454
Okay.
You get!

09:47.487 --> 09:48.288
[ Door opens ]

09:48.321 --> 09:50.123
[ Whispering ]
I'm so sorry.

09:50.157 --> 09:51.992
Mom, Dad, I just did
a double skid jump!

09:52.025 --> 09:53.293
It was --
Oh, God! No!
Oh, God! Oh!

09:53.326 --> 09:54.294
[ Shrieks ]

09:54.327 --> 09:56.229
It's not --
Oh, no!

09:56.263 --> 09:57.397
Buddy, you're dreaming!
Shameful and bad! Oh, God!

09:57.430 --> 09:58.331
Why?!
You're dreaming.
[ Door slams ]

09:58.365 --> 09:59.566
Rio: This is crazy.
[ Chicken clucks ]

09:59.599 --> 10:01.935
We get no dinner,
no house.

10:01.969 --> 10:03.971
It is shockingly
cold in here.

10:04.004 --> 10:06.406
You know, we just wanted
one night away from everybody.
I know.

10:06.439 --> 10:08.341
And now they're inside
eating our goose.

10:08.375 --> 10:09.176
I know. It's your goose.
And we're in a barn...

10:09.209 --> 10:10.678
I know, sweetie.
...without a toilet.

10:10.711 --> 10:13.580
Just like Santa,
right?
How's that?

10:13.613 --> 10:15.082
You know, it's like Santa
went up to the North Pole

10:15.115 --> 10:16.750
and he turned into a reindeer
and then he came on down.

10:16.784 --> 10:17.484
That's exactly it.

10:17.517 --> 10:18.485
Was it?
Yeah.

10:18.518 --> 10:20.320
At least we're alone.
Yeah.

10:20.353 --> 10:21.655
I mean, no one's gonna find us
out here in this barn.

10:21.689 --> 10:23.590
Ah, sorry!

10:23.623 --> 10:25.125
Oh, my God.
Jacob!

10:25.158 --> 10:27.160
Do you guys have anything that
I can gouge my eyes out with?

10:27.194 --> 10:29.429
What's going on?
I saw my parents having sex.

10:29.462 --> 10:30.664
Oh, yikes.
Wow.

10:30.698 --> 10:31.832
The whole house smelled
like an iguana tank,

10:31.865 --> 10:33.333
and we do not have
an iguana.

10:33.366 --> 10:35.135
Oh, God.

10:35.168 --> 10:38.338
Do not tell my parents
that I'm here.

10:38.371 --> 10:39.606
Hold on a second.
I'm never going home again!

10:39.639 --> 10:42.009
This is ridiculous, because
now we're not even alone.

10:42.042 --> 10:43.176
No, I know!
So I'm gonna tell you
right now,

10:43.210 --> 10:44.778
I'm going in
to get some goose.

10:44.812 --> 10:47.715
I'll be damned if I don't get
at least a goose leg.

10:47.748 --> 10:49.216
Yeah, I'll be damned
if you're damned!

10:49.249 --> 10:50.617
Go get your goose,
baby!

10:50.650 --> 10:52.352
I hate everything!

10:52.385 --> 10:54.321
Uh, good luck
with that.
Yeah. Thanks.

10:54.354 --> 10:55.889
Hey, Jacob,
I'm coming up there, okay?

10:55.923 --> 10:56.990
No!

10:58.926 --> 11:00.560
Hey, buddy.

11:03.230 --> 11:05.065
Hi.

11:05.098 --> 11:06.533
I like your sweater.

11:06.566 --> 11:08.135
Oh.
You look really pretty.

11:08.168 --> 11:09.803
Thanks, Jacob.
Very sweet.

11:09.837 --> 11:11.004
[ Sighs ]

11:11.038 --> 11:12.539
Listen,
do you want to talk?

11:12.572 --> 11:14.674
My dad has so much hair
on his back...
Oh.

11:14.708 --> 11:16.143
...and mom was using it
like a handle.

11:16.176 --> 11:18.511
Ooh.
I saw both their tongues!

11:18.545 --> 11:20.147
Oh, wow.
It looked like
they were hurting each other,

11:20.180 --> 11:22.382
but they were smiling.
Yeah, this is --

11:22.415 --> 11:24.551
Is that regular?
Is that normal?
Listen.

11:24.584 --> 11:25.685
I can't imagine
what that's like.

11:25.719 --> 11:27.154
It's a lot.

11:27.187 --> 11:29.056
It's upsetting
to process all this.

11:29.089 --> 11:30.257
Hey, do you want
to go to Main Street

11:30.290 --> 11:31.491
and watch me do skids?

11:31.524 --> 11:33.493
No, thank you.
I'm really awesome at them.

11:33.526 --> 11:34.661
I'm sure.
Can I kiss you?

11:34.694 --> 11:36.663
No. No, no, no, no.

11:36.696 --> 11:38.265
I think I'm in love with you.
Okay, you're not --

11:38.298 --> 11:40.033
No, no, no.
I want to marry Janine.

11:40.067 --> 11:42.035
You've got a lot
of emotions

11:42.069 --> 11:43.670
that are wrestling
with each other.

11:43.703 --> 11:45.839
You got to process --
Rio, can I ask you a question?

11:45.873 --> 11:47.540
You can ask me a question.

11:47.574 --> 11:49.176
But if it has to do
with kissing

11:49.209 --> 11:51.378
or anything romantic,
the answer is no.

11:51.411 --> 11:52.746
Uh-huh.
Okay?
So, that's not gonna change.

11:52.780 --> 11:53.781
What's your question?

11:56.917 --> 11:58.451
Merry Christmas.

11:58.485 --> 12:00.253
Merry Christmas.

12:00.287 --> 12:01.955
Good question.
[ Door opens ]

12:01.989 --> 12:03.757
Rudy: That was back
when I was a Wall Street bigwig.

12:03.791 --> 12:05.458
I rode around
in a limo made of gold,

12:05.492 --> 12:07.694
which was very heavy
and slow.

12:07.727 --> 12:08.695
[ Silverware clinks softly ]

12:08.728 --> 12:10.864
He's stealing!

12:10.898 --> 12:12.099
Aah!

12:12.132 --> 12:13.633
Hey!
Go get yourself a job!

12:13.666 --> 12:15.302
You ought to be
ashamed of yourself.

12:15.335 --> 12:17.237
Rudy does
so much for you.

12:17.270 --> 12:19.739
And after you were
irresponsible enough

12:19.773 --> 12:21.608
to lose your farm.

12:21.641 --> 12:24.077
You are pathetic.

12:27.347 --> 12:29.817
She's right.
You're pathetic.

12:29.850 --> 12:30.984
You'll always
be pathetic,

12:31.018 --> 12:32.619
living a life
like that.

12:32.652 --> 12:35.588
**

12:35.622 --> 12:38.158
You know, Belle...

12:38.191 --> 12:42.062
you may judge me
for living in a barn,

12:42.095 --> 12:45.065
but I am way more than
a list of the things I own.

12:45.098 --> 12:47.134
I'm an incredible person.

12:47.167 --> 12:48.802
And I think
if you got to know me,

12:48.836 --> 12:51.939
you would love me the same way
that Constance loves me.
What?

12:51.972 --> 12:53.440
You're in love
with this guy, too?

12:53.473 --> 12:54.407
No, she needs
to hear the truth.

12:54.441 --> 12:55.642
Rudy...

12:55.675 --> 12:57.077
I'm the one
that lives in a barn.

12:57.110 --> 12:58.778
Mike and his wife,
Rio, live here.

12:58.812 --> 13:00.413
I'm jobless,
I have $10 to my name,

13:00.447 --> 13:01.949
and my best friend
is a goat.

13:01.982 --> 13:04.151
Yesterday, I had a handful
of loose sugar for dinner.

13:04.184 --> 13:08.121
Constance Lucretia
Byrd Terry...

13:08.155 --> 13:09.356
I'm ashamed of you.

13:09.389 --> 13:10.958
Now box up that goose,

13:10.991 --> 13:13.493
get your things,
and let's go.

13:13.526 --> 13:16.663
[ Wheelchair beeps, whirs,
thuds ]

13:18.398 --> 13:21.034
[ Thud ]

13:21.068 --> 13:24.104
[ Wheelchair beeps, whirs ]

13:24.137 --> 13:25.772
[ Object crashes ]

13:25.805 --> 13:27.640
Rudy, she's just tired.

13:27.674 --> 13:29.376
She goes to bed at 3:00.

13:29.409 --> 13:31.378
I will calm her down.

13:31.411 --> 13:33.513
Belle: Constance,
don't make me wheel myself home.

13:33.546 --> 13:35.348
I'm sorry that I lied.
I was ashamed.

13:35.382 --> 13:37.317
Those were very nice things
you said about yourself.

13:37.350 --> 13:38.651
Yeah.

13:38.685 --> 13:40.187
I was talking about
my friend Rudy.

13:40.220 --> 13:41.821
I thought so.
I just wanted to be sure.

13:41.855 --> 13:43.290
I've got some crying
to do,

13:43.323 --> 13:44.324
and you probably
don't want to hear that.

13:44.357 --> 13:46.026
Do you want this pillow?

13:46.059 --> 13:47.394
Thank you.
Yeah.

13:47.427 --> 13:47.995
I'll leave you to it.

13:49.562 --> 13:51.498
[ Sobbing ]

13:51.531 --> 13:53.400
Merry Christmas!

13:53.433 --> 13:54.534
Rio:
Your parents are here.

13:54.567 --> 13:56.836
Jacob: I've seen enough
of them today!

13:56.870 --> 13:58.205
Son, just -- just --
just come down here.

13:58.238 --> 13:59.739
Kay: Jacob,
this is ridiculous!
Come here. Come here.

13:59.772 --> 14:01.808
Nothing even happened.
You were hallucinating.

14:01.841 --> 14:03.476
I wish
I was hallucinating!
Okay, okay.

14:03.510 --> 14:06.046
Li-- Yeah, I think we should,
you know, find truth

14:06.079 --> 14:07.514
when speaking
to our children.

14:07.547 --> 14:08.648
Are you guys
getting back together?

14:08.681 --> 14:09.682
No.
We're not?

14:09.716 --> 14:11.218
Well, you tell me.
You tell me!

14:11.251 --> 14:12.752
I can't listen to this anymore!

14:12.785 --> 14:14.087
I'm never coming home,

14:14.121 --> 14:15.088
I'm going to Hollywood,

14:15.122 --> 14:16.556
and I'm gonna work
in show business.

14:16.589 --> 14:18.325
The hell you are, boy!

14:18.358 --> 14:21.261
I'm gonna go to --
to Wall Street
and be on Broadway.

14:21.294 --> 14:22.930
Where are my savings bonds?

14:22.963 --> 14:24.497
You're not going
to show business...
Well --

14:24.531 --> 14:26.833
and you're not
cashing those bonds
until you're 21!

14:26.866 --> 14:28.035
We're gonna stay in this barn
all night long!

14:28.068 --> 14:29.903
Do you hear me?
We are never gonna leave!

14:29.937 --> 14:32.339
We're spending Christmas
together, like a family!

14:32.372 --> 14:33.941
We're never gonna talk
about what happened!

14:33.974 --> 14:35.342
Hey, now, boy!

14:35.375 --> 14:36.709
Oh, my God.
Geez.
You watch yourself!

14:36.743 --> 14:37.945
That is a lot of anger.
[ Cellphone chimes,
ladder thuds ]

14:37.978 --> 14:39.179
And I don't know
where you get it!

14:39.212 --> 14:41.081
Stop that ladder right there!
Put that back!

14:41.114 --> 14:42.249
You leave that ladder
right there!

14:42.282 --> 14:43.883
This seems good.
[ Indistinct arguing ]

14:43.917 --> 14:45.052
Kee-- Stay in it.
You're not going
to Hollywood!

14:45.085 --> 14:47.020
[ Arguing continues ]

14:47.054 --> 14:49.422
I'll just run up there!
Get out of my way!

14:49.456 --> 14:52.926
**

14:52.960 --> 14:54.461
Great news.
Okay.

14:54.494 --> 14:57.364
I found a Boston Market
40 minutes from here.
Ooh!

14:57.397 --> 14:59.199
Great, and you know what?
They're gonna be fine.

14:59.232 --> 15:00.433
They're fine.
[ Barn door opens ]

15:00.467 --> 15:01.634
They're -- They're --
They're gonna manage this --

15:01.668 --> 15:03.136
Kay: Jacob!

15:03.170 --> 15:04.404
Beau: It's not -- It's not
what you think!
Jacob!

15:04.437 --> 15:05.372
Don't you throttle that!
[ Engine starts, revs ]

15:05.405 --> 15:07.540
Your mother was
checking me for ticks!

15:07.574 --> 15:09.977
Oh, my God.
Are you kidding me?!

15:10.010 --> 15:10.978
You seduced me.

15:11.011 --> 15:12.212
Kay: I couldn't help it!
Um...

15:12.245 --> 15:13.446
Came in hot
with all those chores.

15:13.480 --> 15:14.948
What do you think I'm gonna do,
keep my pants on?

15:19.219 --> 15:20.553
Nothing like a long drive
to a fast-food restaurant
on Christmas, right?

15:21.688 --> 15:22.722
That's right.
That's right.

15:22.755 --> 15:24.257
Whatever drama
that they have going on

15:24.291 --> 15:26.393
is their drama exclusively.
Yeah, that's them.
That's them.

15:26.426 --> 15:28.595
It's -- It's not ours, so --
No. Everyone here is an adult.

15:28.628 --> 15:30.497
I'm not taking it on.
I'm not taking --
We're guilt-free.
We'll go.

15:30.530 --> 15:31.831
Hey!
Help! Help!

15:31.864 --> 15:33.500
I can hear a dre--
We need a third

15:33.533 --> 15:35.135
to go find Jacob!
I can hear Rudy
crying inside your house!

15:35.168 --> 15:36.136
You gotta do something!
Okay.

15:36.169 --> 15:36.903
We need someone to talk to.
Please, Rio!

15:36.936 --> 15:38.771
Okay.
Hey!

15:38.805 --> 15:40.007
Let's at least take...
What's the holdup?!

15:40.040 --> 15:41.008
...five seconds
of alone time.
Hey, guys!

15:41.841 --> 15:42.509
Guys.

15:42.542 --> 15:45.078
Please, we need you!

15:45.112 --> 15:46.946
No, it's Christmas!
All right!

15:46.980 --> 15:47.580
It ain't kissy time!
We don't have time for this!

15:47.614 --> 15:48.748
Hey!
Hey!

15:48.781 --> 15:50.283
Let's divide and conquer it.
Okay.

15:50.317 --> 15:51.118
I'll do Constance --
You go to Connie's.
I'm gonna get -- Yeah.

15:51.151 --> 15:52.119
Yeah, okay. Okay.
[ Knock on door ]

15:52.152 --> 15:53.953
Oh, Mike.
Hi.

15:53.987 --> 15:56.256
Constance, uh,
can we talk about this?

15:56.289 --> 15:57.490
Just keep it down.

15:57.524 --> 15:58.591
Mom's in the back room,

15:58.625 --> 16:00.193
watching "Succession"
on her tablet.

16:00.227 --> 16:01.528
Okay.
Please, how's Rudy?

16:01.561 --> 16:03.796
Tell him I'll talk to him
after my mama leaves.

16:03.830 --> 16:06.099
You know how you usually
give us tough love?

16:06.133 --> 16:07.834
Well, I'm here to give you
some tough love.

16:07.867 --> 16:09.202
Pretend I'm you.

16:09.236 --> 16:12.105
Now, what would you tell you
in this situation?

16:12.139 --> 16:14.007
I know I should
stand up to my mama.

16:14.041 --> 16:15.942
But after not doing it
for so many years,

16:15.975 --> 16:18.278
I don't know why
I should start now.

16:18.311 --> 16:20.213
I think Rudy is --
is the "why."

16:20.247 --> 16:22.882
You know, if I'm you,
I don't want to lose him.

16:22.915 --> 16:24.784
I thought I was being me.

16:24.817 --> 16:27.187
Yes, exactly.
You are being you.

16:27.220 --> 16:29.456
Constance is Mike.
What?

16:29.489 --> 16:31.624
So what would Constance-you
tell Mike-yourself?

16:31.658 --> 16:34.327
I'd say, "Constance,
get your head out your ass."

16:34.361 --> 16:35.628
Boom.

16:35.662 --> 16:36.963
And it sounds so good
when you say it.

16:36.996 --> 16:38.998
[ Sighs ]

16:39.032 --> 16:40.133
Kay: It just happened,
okay, Beau?
Beau: I know.

16:40.167 --> 16:41.168
I wasn't thinking
about it.

16:41.201 --> 16:43.136
I just felt an urge,
and I went for it,

16:43.170 --> 16:45.338
and you reciprocated,
and there we were.

16:45.372 --> 16:46.339
Well, I just wish
you would tell me

16:46.373 --> 16:47.874
what you want it to mean.

16:47.907 --> 16:48.908
Well, I don't know
what it means

16:48.941 --> 16:50.343
that we threw a nickel
into the old arcade.

16:50.377 --> 16:51.811
Guys, this is
really good stuff.
[ Sighs ]

16:51.844 --> 16:53.346
Don't be afraid
to be vulnerable,

16:53.380 --> 16:55.848
because communication is
the pathway to breakthrough.

16:55.882 --> 16:57.884
Your volume is
so annoying.

16:57.917 --> 16:59.219
This is why people
don't do therapy,

16:59.252 --> 17:00.553
'cause you're just
[Whispers indistinctly]

17:00.587 --> 17:01.554
I can't hear you!

17:01.588 --> 17:02.889
If you regret it,
just tell me,

17:02.922 --> 17:04.424
and I can handle it.

17:04.457 --> 17:06.259
I don't regret it, Beau.
Oh, my God.

17:06.293 --> 17:07.327
There's one thing
I'm sure of.

17:07.360 --> 17:08.428
I --

17:08.461 --> 17:10.029
I loved it.

17:10.063 --> 17:11.831
[ Chuckling ] You did?

17:11.864 --> 17:13.400
Yeah.

17:13.433 --> 17:15.502
So did I.

17:15.535 --> 17:17.170
Rio, what does that mean?
Tell us what it means, huh?

17:17.204 --> 17:18.538
What-- What's it mean?

17:18.571 --> 17:19.739
So, as a therapist,

17:19.772 --> 17:21.408
it's not my job to kinda
tell you how you feel.

17:21.441 --> 17:22.842
That's up to you.

17:22.875 --> 17:24.544
Then why the hell would anyone
go to a therapist?

17:24.577 --> 17:26.546
And then why do they
call you guys "life's referee"?

17:26.579 --> 17:27.914
They don't.

17:27.947 --> 17:29.916
Rio, just tell us what it means!
Just tell us, please.

17:29.949 --> 17:31.284
Stop.
Why are you putting us
through this?

17:31.318 --> 17:32.719
Stop, stop, stop, stop, stop.
[ Snaps fingers ] Jacob.

17:32.752 --> 17:34.020
There he is.
Beau and Kay: Oh!

17:34.053 --> 17:35.688
See, he's doing
the sad-boy donuts over there.

17:35.722 --> 17:37.457
Just pull over.

17:37.490 --> 17:39.459
Guys, you can just be
glad that it happened,

17:39.492 --> 17:41.761
be open to your future,
and keep communicating, okay?

17:41.794 --> 17:43.296
Finally.
Took you long enough.

17:43.330 --> 17:45.298
Guys.
Huh?

17:45.332 --> 17:46.966
This is where
you go talk to Jacob.

17:46.999 --> 17:48.135
[ Sighs ]

17:48.168 --> 17:49.569
**

17:49.602 --> 17:50.470
Guys.
What?

17:50.503 --> 17:51.604
Go. Talk to him.

17:51.638 --> 17:53.206
[ Groans ]

17:53.240 --> 17:54.707
It's gonna be hard
to make eye contact with him

17:54.741 --> 17:56.143
after he saw
what we were doing.

17:56.176 --> 17:57.577
It was something
I saw on Facebook.

17:57.610 --> 17:58.911
I reported it,

17:58.945 --> 18:00.980
but then it really
stuck with me.

18:01.013 --> 18:02.549
Belle: Wait.

18:02.582 --> 18:04.083
What's he doing here?

18:04.117 --> 18:05.985
It's that son of a bitch
with the goose.

18:06.018 --> 18:08.321
Mama, there's something
you need to hear.

18:08.355 --> 18:11.791
Rudy is a fantastic man
who's --
[ Door opens ]

18:11.824 --> 18:13.226
Constance, I'm sorry
for the intrusion.

18:13.260 --> 18:15.262
Mrs. Byrd,
I do have an asset --

18:15.295 --> 18:17.096
a Lou Gehrig baseball card
in mint condition.

18:17.130 --> 18:19.832
It would go for
$3- or $4 million.

18:19.866 --> 18:21.234
And I know it's real
because I bought it

18:21.268 --> 18:23.770
from a reliable young man
in a tie-dye blazer.

18:23.803 --> 18:26.639
Constance, this man
cannot take care of you.

18:26.673 --> 18:30.977
The value of baseball cards
is plummeting every day.

18:31.010 --> 18:33.280
You've met Rio's mom.

18:33.313 --> 18:34.681
If I can do that,
you can do this.

18:34.714 --> 18:36.916
[ Inhales deeply ]

18:36.949 --> 18:38.285
No, Mom.

18:38.318 --> 18:41.488
I don't need a man
to take care of me.

18:41.521 --> 18:43.022
You should know
because you taught me

18:43.055 --> 18:44.324
how to take care
of myself.

18:44.357 --> 18:46.293
The only thing I need
from a man is love,

18:46.326 --> 18:49.162
and he's got --
he's got plenty of that to give.

18:49.196 --> 18:50.930
Oh. [ Chuckles ]

18:50.963 --> 18:52.299
So back off...

18:52.332 --> 18:54.234
ma'am.

18:55.402 --> 18:58.171
Also, ma'am,
and I can't say this enough,

18:58.205 --> 19:00.173
there was no need
for you to see my genitals.

19:00.207 --> 19:02.442
That is, and shall remain,
my bad.

19:02.475 --> 19:05.144
Constance, I cannot believe
you're defying me.

19:05.178 --> 19:07.647
But love is love, apparently.

19:07.680 --> 19:10.149
Otherwise, I don't know
why you would choose him.

19:10.183 --> 19:12.685
Well, I guess I do know
one reason.

19:12.719 --> 19:15.688
That was
quite the Christmas bow.

19:15.722 --> 19:16.856
[ Clicks tongue ]

19:16.889 --> 19:19.526
I see you, girl.
I see you.

19:19.559 --> 19:26.866
* Have yourself
a merry little Christmas *

19:26.899 --> 19:33.373
* Let your heart be light

19:33.406 --> 19:37.244
* Next year, all our troubles

19:37.277 --> 19:43.583
* Will be out of sight

19:57.096 --> 19:57.997
This is nice, you know.
Just the two of us.

19:59.632 --> 20:00.833
Finally.
Yeah, all alone --
just you, me,

20:00.867 --> 20:01.834
and -- and a goose.

20:01.868 --> 20:03.002
That's what we wanted,
right?

20:03.035 --> 20:04.604
That was our Christmas wish,
right?
Yeah.

20:04.637 --> 20:06.339
And Chris-- Christmas,
you get a wish, right?

20:06.373 --> 20:07.440
Don't you get a wish?

20:07.474 --> 20:09.075
Yeah, you --
you get a Christmas wish.

20:09.108 --> 20:10.777
Mm-hmm.
Yeah.

20:10.810 --> 20:13.079
Hmm. [ Sighs ]

20:19.419 --> 20:20.953
Do you miss them at all?
Yes!

20:20.987 --> 20:22.889
[ Laughter ]

20:22.922 --> 20:25.124
Four extra deer,
and he said Santa --

20:25.157 --> 20:26.259
Santa's been
drinking again.

20:26.293 --> 20:27.927
[ Laughter ]

20:27.960 --> 20:30.129
Well, he broke the law.
Santa broke the law.
Jacob: Oh, yeah!

20:30.162 --> 20:31.964
Beau: I have not
heard that one.

20:31.998 --> 20:33.132
How you doing, buddy?

20:33.165 --> 20:34.867
Oh, I'm fine.
Mm-hmm.

20:34.901 --> 20:35.735
I really like
your apron.

20:35.768 --> 20:37.270
It's got nice eyes.

20:37.304 --> 20:38.405
Mike: Okay, there, Jacob.
Oh. Okay. [ Chuckles ]

20:38.438 --> 20:40.273
I brought
the custard I made.

20:40.307 --> 20:42.309
Time has not been kind to it.
It's a bit runny.

20:42.342 --> 20:44.577
It's more of a nog than a pie,
but it looks delicious.

20:44.611 --> 20:46.078
It is like a nog.
I can't wait
to ladle out some.

20:46.112 --> 20:47.079
Uh-oh!
Uh-oh.

20:47.113 --> 20:48.448
Hey, hey, hey!
Hup! Hup! Hup!

20:48.481 --> 20:49.916
Hup! Hup!

20:49.949 --> 20:51.618
I can't believe
we were gonna do this alone.

20:51.651 --> 20:53.085
I know.

20:53.119 --> 20:54.554
This is the perfect
first Bucksnort Christmas.

20:54.587 --> 20:56.055
[ Glass clinks ]

20:56.088 --> 20:59.091
I am so thankful
to be here with Rudy...
Mm.

20:59.125 --> 21:00.660
...my mom, and all of you.

21:00.693 --> 21:02.094
Aww.
My family.

21:02.128 --> 21:03.330
Thanks.

21:03.363 --> 21:05.298
You think
we're family?

21:05.332 --> 21:06.733
Well, duh.
Yes. Yes.

21:06.766 --> 21:07.834
[ Chuckles ]

21:07.867 --> 21:09.936
[ Chuckles ]
To family?

21:09.969 --> 21:11.404
I like that. Sure.
To family.

21:11.438 --> 21:12.405
-Family.
-Hear, hear.

21:12.439 --> 21:13.640
-Absolutely.
-Hear, hear.

21:13.673 --> 21:14.441
-Round the horn. There we go.
-There we go.

21:14.474 --> 21:16.108
Rudy...

21:16.142 --> 21:18.010
when do we get
to eat this goat?

21:18.044 --> 21:19.512
[ Theresa bleats ]
Constance: No.

21:19.546 --> 21:20.680
Manners, Theresa.

21:20.713 --> 21:21.948
Eat your Christmas turnip.

21:21.981 --> 21:23.282
[ Laughter ]
Rio: What?

21:23.316 --> 21:24.384
[ Theresa bleats ]
